725054f-b.title: Queens: 19th Avenue - 47th Street
725054f-b.text:
19th Ave., between 47th Street and Bowery Bay, (Note all area
under water in views 2 and 3 is now dry land upon which streets have
been constructed.) showing at the east end of the former Luyster
Island the D.S. Riker house, in a set of three views.
May 1923.
View 2: March 1925.
View 3: May 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725055f-b.title: Queens: 19th Avenue - 47th Street
725055f-b.text:
Eineteenth Ave., north side, between 47th and 48th Streets, showing
on the east end of Luyster's Island, the Riker house. This island is now
a part of the mainland. H. Riker and D.S. Riker were owners in 1852 and
1891 respectively. The house seen in this set of three views was destroyed
by fire about 1929. The house erected on Riker's Island was erected by
Andrew Riker in the late 18th Century.
May 1923.
Views 1 \& 2.
View 3: March 1923.
View 4: June 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
